(1947–1967), the auteur renaissance (1968–1980), the New Hollywood (1981–1999), and the modern entertainment marketplace (2000–present). The contributors pay special attention to definitive performances by notable film stars, including Lillian Gish, Dick Powell, Ginger Rogers, Beulah Bondi, Marilyn Monroe, Marlon Brando, Jack Nicholson, Robert De Niro, Nicholas Cage, Denzel Washington, and Andy Serkis. In six original essays, the contributors to this volume illuminate the dynamic role of acting in the creation and evolving practices of the American film industry. Acting is a volume in the Behind the Silver Screen series—other titles in the series include Animation; Art Direction and Production Design; Cinematography; Costume, Makeup, and Hair; Directing; Editing and Special/Visual Effects; Producing; Screenwriting; and Sound.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMotion picture acting. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  ascreen performance, performing arts, acting, audition, actor, actress, silver screen, social science, media studies, film, video, communications, history of film, film acting, performer, performance, vaudeville, wild west, hollywood, cgi, athlete, audience, movie goers, silent screen, classical hollywood, postwar hollywood, auteur renaissance, new hollywood, modern entertainment marketplace, entertainment, lillian gish, dick powell, ginger rogers, beulah bondi, marilyn monroe, marlon brando, jack nicholson, robert de niro, nicholas cage, denzel washington, andy serkis, academy awards, oscars.1 aBaron, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaron, Cynthia.1 aDuckett, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuckett, Victoria.1 aLevinson, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevinson, J